.Dd Nov 12, 2025
.Dt gufi_find
.Os Linux
.Sh NAME
.Nm gufi_find
.Nd GUFI version of GNU
.Xr find 1
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op -P
.Op path
.Op expression
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a wrapper around
.Xr gufi_query 1 , which performs queries on the contents of a GUFI index in a parallel manner. The queries that are passed into
.Xr gufi_query 1 are predefined pieces that are deterministically combined.

The input arguments and output are intended to be reminicent of GNU
.Xr find 1 .

.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It Fl h, -help
show this help message and exit
.It Fl -version, v
show program's version number and exit
.It Fl amin\ n
File was last accessed n minutes ago.
.It Fl atime\ n
File was last accessed n*24 hours ago.
.It Fl cmin\ n
File's status was last changed n minutes ago.
.It Fl ctime\ n
File's status was last changed n*24 hours ago.
.It Fl empty
File is empty and is either a regular file or a directory.
.It Fl executable
Matches files which are executable and directories which are searchable (in a file name resolution sense).
.It Fl false
File is false and is either a regular file or a directory.
.It Fl gid\ n
File's numeric group ID is n.
.It Fl group\ gname
File belongs to group gname (numeric group ID allowed).
.It Fl iname\ pattern
Like name, but the match is case insensitive.
.It Fl inum\ n
File has inode number n. It is normally easier to use the -samefile test instead.
.It Fl links\ n
File has n links.
.It Fl lname\ pattern
File is a symbolic link whose contents match shell pattern pattern.
.It Fl mmin\ n
File's data was last modified n minutes ago.
.It Fl mtime\ n
File's data was last modified n*24 hours ago.
.It Fl name\ pattern
Base of file name (the path with the leading directories removed) matches shell pattern pattern.
.It Fl newer\ file
File was modified more recently than file.
.It Fl path\ pattern
File name matches shell pattern pattern.
.It Fl readable
Matches files which are readable.
.It Fl samefile\ name
File refers to the same inode as name.
.It Fl size\ n
.It Fl true
Always true
.It Fl type\ c
File is of type c
.It Fl uid\ n
File's numeric user ID is n.
.It Fl user\ uname
File is owned by user uname (numeric user ID allowed).
.It Fl writable
Matches files which are writable.
.It Fl maxdepth\ levels
Descend at most levels (a non-negative integer) levels of directories below the command line arguments. -maxdepth 0 means only apply the tests and actions to the command line arguments.
.It Fl mindepth\ levels
Do not apply any tests or actions at levels less than levels (a non-negative integer). mindepth 1 means process all files except the command line arguments.
.It Fl fprint\ file
Output file prefix
.It Fl ls
list current file ls -dils format
.It Fl print
print the full name on the standard output, followed by a newline, similar to GNU find
.It Fl print0
print the full name on the standard output, followed by a null character, similar to GNU find
.It Fl -delim\ c
delimiter separating output columns
.It Fl -size%\ n\ n
Modifier to the size flag. Expects 2 values that define the min and max percentage from the size.
.It Fl -num-results\ n
first n results
.It Fl -smallest\ n
top n smallest files
.It Fl -largest\ n
top n largest files
.It Fl -compress
try to reduce memory usage by compressing with zlib (if available)
.El

.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width -indent
.It EXIT_SUCCESS or EXIT_FAILURE
.El

.Pp
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width -compact
.It gufi_find
.It @INSTALL_CONFIG@
.El

